==English==
===Etymology1===
Old French ''soper''
====Verb====
'''sup'''
# to take [[supper]].
===Etymology2===
[[aphetic]] form of '''[[what's up]]'''; [[Sup]]? = [[What's up]]? = How are you doing?
====Interjection====
'''sup?'''
#(''slang'') a superinformal greeting.
#: '''''Sup?''' : (response) [[Nuch]].''
=====Synonyms=====
*[[wassup]]
*[[wudup]]
